<h2>About the Creative Commons Music Sharing License</h2>

<p>The Creative Commons music license helps you:</p>	

<ol style="font-size:24px;font-weight:bold;">
<li>
<p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:normal;margin-left:0px;line-height:150%;"><strong>Mark It Legal</strong>: 
Mark your music with the CC logo so fans know that you own your copyright, but give permission to download, file-share, copy, and webcast &mdash; but not to sell, alter, or make any other commercial uses. <a href="http://mirrors.creativecommons.org/metamatt/">Here's an example</a> of how it would look on a band's web page and <a href="/learn/licenses/music-comics">here's a short comic</a> describing how fans might legally use your music.</p></li>
<li>
<p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:normal;margin-left:0px;line-height:150%;"><strong>Promote It</strong>: Register your music at <a href="http://commoncontent.org">Common Content</a> so people can contact you to purchase commercial rights to the composition or sound recording. Or, <a href="http://archive.org/audio/collection.php?collection=opensource_audio">have it hosted for free</a> at the Internet Archive.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p style="font-size:11px;font-weight:normal;margin-left:0px;line-height:150%;"><strong>Make It Searchable</strong>: Make your music searchable within <a href="http://search.creativecommons.org/">the Creative Commons audio search engine</a>.</p></li>
</ol>

